{"metadata":{"platforms":[{"name":"Brunow","introducedAt":"2017.01.20"}],"modules":[{"name":"Brunow"}],"title":"Corporate and Football Penalties","color":{"standardColorIdentifier":"purple"}},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow","doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/Archive","doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/2015"]]},"topicSectionsStyle":"detailedGrid","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/brunow\/06-07-corporate-and-football-penalties"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"sections":[],"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/06-07-corporate-and-football-penalties","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"date: 2015-06-07T21:55:14-05:00"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"What if the penalties in football were more like the penalties in the corporate world? What if, instead of negating any forward progress, penalties were simply subtracted from the gains?"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This would create a remarkably different game. There’d be penalties on every down! A holding call on a 15 yard run would result in a 10 yard gain. Penalties would no longer be a deterrent to illegal play, they’d just be part of a good strategy.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow/Archive":{"role":"collectionGroup","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"All posts"}],"title":"Archive","identifier":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/Archive","type":"topic","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/brunow\/archive"},"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow/2015":{"abstract":[],"role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/brunow\/2015","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/2015","title":"2015"},"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow":{"url":"\/documentation\/brunow","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"David Brunow, known as Brunow [ˈbɹunoʊ] to the folks he works with, is a human living on Earth. You might have something in common with him — if you think it is ridiculous that he is talking about himself in the first person here, so does he.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","title":"Brunow"}}}